def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    levels = []
    codes = []
    names = []

    for cloc in clocs:
        if isinstance(cloc, tuple):
            level = index._get_level_number(cloc[0])
            sub_level = cloc[1]
            levels.append(index.levels[level])
            codes.append(index.codes[level])
            names.append(cloc)
        else:
            level = index._get_level_number(cloc)
            levels.append(index.levels[level])
            codes.append(index.codes[level])
            names.append(index.names[level])

    shape = [len(x) for x in levels]
    group_index = get_group_index(codes, shape, sort=False, xnull=False)

    comp_ids, obs_ids = compress_group_index(group_index, sort=False)
    recons_codes = decons_obs_group_ids(comp_ids, obs_ids, shape, codes, xnull=False)

    dummy_index = MultiIndex(
        levels=levels + [obs_ids],
        codes=recons_codes + [comp_ids],
        names=names + ["__placeholder__"],
        verify_integrity=False,
    )

    if isinstance(data, Series):
        dummy = data.copy()
        dummy.index = dummy_index
        unstacked = dummy.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)
    else:
        dummy = data.copy()
        dummy.index = dummy_index
        unstacked = dummy.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)

    return unstacked
